#: addons/Accurate_Europe_1_3.wad/addon:4 input:8 input:9 input:10 standard
msgid "Accurate Europe 1.3"
msgstr "Akkerates Europa 1.3"

#: addons/Accurate_Europe_1_3.wad/dirnames:4 input:4 standard
msgid "Add-On Maps"
msgstr "Verwiederns-Kaarten"

#: input:6 standard
msgid ""
"Warning: This map is provided as an experimental preview. Although it is "
"better in many ways than Europa 1.2 that it replaces, it probably still has "
"bugs. Furthermore, it is a very large map with more player positions than "
"generally recommended, so it has high hardware requirements.  — <br> <br> "
"<br>A map for roleplaying historical empires.  <br>– This map of Europe aims "
"to be as accurate as practically possible in Widelands.  <br>– EASY: Ottoman "
"Empire, Sweden, Russian Empire, Carthage  <br>– MEDIUM: French Empire, "
"British Empire, Spain, German Empire, Roman Empire  <br>– HARD: Egypt, "
"Poland, Greece"
msgstr ""
"Wahrschau: Deese Kaart word as noch nich steviger Utkiek klaargeven. Dat is "
"in mennig Aarden beter as Europa 1.2, wat ’t utwesselt, enthollt man aver "
"wull noch Fehlers. Daarto is dat eene bannig grote Kaart mit mehr Spelers, "
"as normaal anraden worden, stellt also hooge Anförderns an de Reekner. – "
"<br> <br> <br> Eene Kaart, um histoorisk Rieken natospölen. <br>– Deese "
"Kaart vun Europa versöcht, so akkeraat as in Widelands praktisk mögelk to "
"wesen. <br>– LICHT: Ottomaansk Riek, Sweden, Russisk Riek, Kartago <br>– "
"MIDDEL: Frankriek, Engelks Riek, Spaanje, Düütsches Riek, Römisk Riek <br>– "
"STUUV: Ägypten, Polen, Grekenland"

#: input:7 standard
msgid ""
"The wide rivers are navigable to create a ”trade network”.  <br>All players "
"have their own challenges, but are relatively balanced to be playable:  "
"<br>– British Empire: create sustainable colonies  <br>– Russian Empire: "
"Very large distances …"
msgstr ""
"Up de wieden Stromen is Seefahrt mögelk, um een »Hannelsnett« uptobauen. "
"<br>All Spelers hebben hör eegen Rutfödderungen, sünd aver eenigermaten "
"utgleken, um spöölbaar to wesen: <br>– Engelsk Riek: sett versörgbaare "
"Kolonien up <br>– Russisk Riek: bannig grote Feernten …"
